Package support.menu

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    BaseCreateMenu
    An extension of BaseListMenu which provides necessary methods for the creation of objects, this could be creating them onto an instance of BookingManager.
    BaseDeleteMenu  
    BaseListMenu
    Extension of BaseMenu which prioritises the displaying of lists over interaction, this can be used to list out specific objects (using their .toString() method), such as Room objects.
    BaseMenu
    BaseMenu is a class that defines a list of options, and a heading, and acts as the primary interface for the user
    BaseMenuOption
    A menu option is an item in a Menu (BaseMenu) which can be either selectable, or not.
    NoOpClass
    Used by the NOOP static option, does absolutely nothing
    SegueOption
    List option which acts as a segue to a given class.
